Package org.jlinalg.demo

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArbitraryPrecisionDemo
    Example that shows how easily simple floating point arithmetic can go wrong.
    CharacteristicPolynomialDemo
    Demonstrate characteristic polynomials for a matrix over the domain of rational numbers.
    EigenvaluesDemo  
    F2Demo
    Demonstrate the use of the F2 data type
    FieldPDemo
    This demonstration of the class FieldP shows that in vector spaces over finite fields there can be linear dependent vectors which are all orthogonal to each other.
    Function
    A target for an optimisation: a 2-degree polynomial in the 3-d Space.
    HilbertMatrixDemo
    This demo shows how the squared distance between the real solution of an equation system to the one that is found when using floating point arithmetic, grows exponentially when the dimension of the Hilbert matrix increases.
    LinearEquationSystemDemo
    Example that computes a solution of a linear equation system for the domain of rational numbers.
    MatrixOperationsDemo
    This computes the determinant and the inverse of a complex matrix.
    PolynomialDemo
    Demonstrate the use of polynomials for the domain of rational numbers.
    RandomGradientSearchDemo
    Demonstrates the use of a RandomGradientDescent to optimise Function.
    RationalFunctionDemo
    Demonstrate the use of rational functions for the domain of rational numbers.
    Xor
    Example showing Exclusive-Or neural net problem using JLinAlg.
